# The toolkit's version, and the only place in the repo that states it by hand.
# toolkit-requirements.lock is generated from this file and pins the whole
# transitive tree with hashes; the Docker image and `just toolkit-setup` both
# install from the lock, never from this file.
#
# The toolkit runs as a subprocess of the prover and is handed the chain's RPC
# URL, so its dependency tree is on the proof path. Pinning only the top-level
# version leaves 60-odd transitive packages resolving fresh on every install.
#
# To bump:
#   1. edit the pin below
#   2. `just toolkit-lock`   (regenerates the lock from a fresh resolve)
#   3. re-verify against the image: `just build`, then import the toolkit
#   4. commit this file and the lock together, never one without the other
votemarket-toolkit==2.0.0
